{
  "texts": [
    "The covariance matrix is then estimated from these 500 realizations of Xℓ, with the elements of the matrix:M ℓ,ij = ⟨ Xℓ,i Xℓ,j ⟩ -⟨ Xℓ,i ⟩⟨ Xℓ,j ⟩(4.11)where Xℓ,i = C obs ℓ for case L0, Xℓ,i = C del ℓ for case L1 and L2, and Xℓ,i ∈ {C obs ℓ, C LT ×obs ℓ, C LT ℓ } for case L3.",
    "The average is taken over 500 simulations.We present the posterior distributions for r and A L using the 4 models with different data in Fig. 9.",
    "The summarized results can be found in Table 2 and Table 3.",
    "In each table, the first and second lines show the result using two models with delensed data (separately L1 and L2), the third line shows the result adding the lensing template map as a new channel to analysis (L3).",
    "Additionally, we provide results based on the data without any delensing process for reference in the last line (L0)."
  ]
}